commit.message:
Re-arrange initializers in MMAPFile to match declaration

The g++ 10 compiler issues a -Wreorder warning about the order of
initializers not matching the order of fields in the structure, and that
the initializers are re-ordered.

Signed-off-by: Zygmunt Krynicki <me@zygoon.pl>
Closes: https://github.com/mgorny/squashdelta/pull/5
Signed-off-by: Michał Górny <mgorny@gentoo.org>

the initializers are re-ordered.

commit.message: Bump to 0.1.1

Deduplicate reused input blocks

Closes: https://github.com/mgorny/squashdelta/issues/3
Support sparse data blocks in squashfs
Add assertions for zero-sized blocks
squashfs: Add constant for zstd compression
Fix offset assertion for adjacent blocks
Fix memory leak
compressor: Fix cloberring return value from lzo compress
Assert for out-of-order compressed blocks
Replace MMAP-based I/O with regular file I/O
MMAPFile: make length member private, in favor of getter
MMAPFile: make data ptr private, use explicit offset getter
MetadataBlockReader: stop using references for output vars
util: Make file class destructors non-throwing
util: Add explicit close() method to file classes

Mark throwing destructors noexcept(false) when compiling in C++11/14 mode

Bug: https://bugs.gentoo.org/595556
Bump PV to 0.1.
List headers in Makefile to fix 'make dist'.
Fix EOF when opening a file with no fragments.
Support lreg inodes.
Switch Compressor.setup() to use MetadataReader code.
Introduce MetadataReader.read().
Move parsing compression options to separate setup() function.
Check whether metadata reads end at block boundary.
LZO: detect whether compressed data was optimized.
Introduce LZ4 support.
Fix sentinel in execlp() call.
LZO: support custom compression level.
